        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 7:00AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 700 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Houlka, or near Houston, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tupelo, Amory, Aberdeen, Houston, Verona, Okolona, Tombigbee State
Park, Shannon, Plantersville, Smithville, Troy, Pyland, New Wren,
Trebloc, Furrs, Houlka, Evergreen, Nettleton, New Houlka, and Algoma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
